when are kittens ready to be adopted my mom's cat had kittens about weels ago she is begining to wean them i heard that if you seperate kitten too early that they will go through seperation anxiety is this true if it is when should we put them up for adoption it is true that kittens seperated too early from their mother and litter mates can develope behavior problems they learn very important lessons from their mother at this time the earliest they can be adopted is weeks but many my vet included believe it is better to wait until they are between weeks kittens learn most things about life and how to behave in their first weeks of life during this time it is important they be socalized and exposed to common things they may run into in their new home this includes small children supervised dogs loud noises a crate the vet car rides everything i would start looking for homes now but do not let the new owners take the kittens until weeks old Kitten Ferret Guinea pig Housebreaking Manx (cat) Dog training Garfield Socialization Pet skunk Dog Hamster Tick Treecat Feral cat Shaggy dog story Randomness Azumanga Daioh Crate training B3ta Domestic rabbit Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Laura Schlessinger Kangaroo Puma Traumatic incident reduction Hearing impairment RuneScape quests Good Times Louis Wain Stuttering The Marshall Mathers LP Pet store Breastfeeding Diazepam Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Friends Red Fox The Beatles bootlegs Phoebe Buffay's songs Purr Cats (musical) Feral Traumatic brain injury Microchip implant (animal) Richard Chase Elizabeth Taylor Siamese (cat) Controversies in autism Autism Japanese Bobtail (cat) Vietnam Veterans Against the War The Aristocats Dog intelligence Lie Minor characters in Teen Titans (animated series) Neighbours Meme Animal communication Drag racing EastEnders Fancy rat Asperger syndrome Mental retardation Red Squirrel Animal euthanasia Doug Scenes from a Memory Cuteness Crash Bandicoot Turkish Angora The Grim Adventures of 